Web application for pick-up basketball

Problem description
	When initially developing the web application the developer implemented a standard authentication,
which required a register. Now, the application has added Google authentication, which is an external
resource, and the sign up for the new log in system must be compatible with the old one, so that the
database doesn't need a reset.
	
Advantages
- existent class which was user before will not be modified
- only a middle ground is added between the two classes

Disadvantages
- the pattern implements multiple derivation which is not available in Java 